though rare for your garage door to open by itself.";i:5;s:72:"There are a few unusual factors that can cause your door open by itself.";i:6;s:42:"Here are a few scenarios weve come across.";i:7;s:144:"Residential electric garage door openers manufactured after 1993 are equipped with two safety mechanisms that operate while the door is closing.";i:8;s:56:"The first is photoelectric and the second is mechanical.";i:9;s:85:"To fix this travel distance locate and change the setting on your garage door opener.";i:10;s:184:"Limit switch malfunctions Similar to the travel setting the limit switch decides where the door stops when its opened or closed if the door reverses direction adjust your limit switch.";i:11;s:40:"Garage door closes but then opens again.";i:12;s:17:"Learn how to fix.";i:13;s:92:"Another easy way to fix a garage door that opens by itself is by checking the remote opener.";i:14;s:100:"If the remote opener is dirty or the batteries are failing it may cause the door to open on its own.";i:15;s:110:"Double check their position or change them out to see if it prevents your garage door from opening on its own.";i:16;s:85:"If your garage door opens and suddenly stops it might be because of your logic board.";i:17;s:60:"The logic board receives and responds signals to any remote.";i:18;s:110:"You might need to consider replacing it if your door is not working properly or you may purchase a new opener.";i:19;s:61:"My liftmaster 3280 garage door opener keeps opening randomly.";i:20;s:142:"We thought it might be that someone in the neighborhood had our same codes so we pressed the learn button for 6 secs to clear out all remotes.";i:21;s:22:"It is still happening.";i:22;s:145:"If your neighbors garage door remote is opening your garage door the first thing to do is reset the codes using the DIP switches or learn button.";i:23;s:140:"If this does not fix the situation then you may need to replace the garage door opener or the circuit board to get to a different frequency.";i:24;s:101:"A garage door that randomly opens by itself is not a common problem but does occur from time to time.";i:25;s:161:"Garage door openers operate on one of many frequencies and while it is possible for one of your neighbors remotes to open your garage door it is highly unlikely.";i:26;s:86:"Newer openers operate on rolling codes making it almost impossible for this to happen.";i:27;s:41:"MyQ garage door opener opening by itself.";i:28;s:53:"I am in a new apartment - so I am the first resident.";i:29;s:168:"I turned on MyQ a couple of days ago and I just noticed in the MyQ app history that the garage door opener has apparently been opening and closing multiple times a day.";i:30;s:87:"If your garage door opener is clicking it is probably also flashing a light on and off.";i:31;s:66:"If this is the case you have likely locked your opener by mistake.";i:32;s:152:"A lot of homeowners will accidentally put their opener into lock mode by sliding a switch or holding a lock button too long on the wall control station.";i:33;s:19:"Garage Door Opener.";i:34;s:27:"Opens and closes by itself.";i:35;s:162:"When your garage door opens or closes when you havent triggered the remote one possible cause is that a neighbors remote was programmed at the same time as yours.";i:36;s:53:"Erase all codes in your remote and then reprogram it.";i:37;s:70:"Your garage doors logic board is the brain of your garage door opener.";i:38;s:64:"This brain can wear out in time so you could need a replacement.";i:39;s:115:"When the logic board wears out it can cause your garage door to close then open and vice versa without explanation.";i:40;s:28:"Get Logic Board Replacement.";i:41;s:57:"Before you break out your toolbox or call a professional.";i:42;s:54:"If the lights stay on I recommend you check the gears.";i:43;s:53:"Replace the gears if there is any problems with them.";i:44;s:119:"Generally if there is a lot of plastic gear shaving inside the garage door opener the door spring needs to be adjusted.";i:45;s:48:"The plastic gears are designed to last 25 years.";i:46;s:18:"I hope this helps.";i:47;s:47:"To order garage door opener parts please visit.";i:48;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:49;s:74:"There may also be loose wire connections inside the button housing itself.";i:50;s:99:"As these wires short against the housing the electrical impulse causes the door opener to activate.";i:51;s:97:"Discovered the problem recently whenever I close my garage door it opens automatically by itself.";i:52;s:94:"Rang service centre and adjusted down limit didnt work at all suggested maybe a motor problem.";i:53;s:152:"Also whenever after it opens automatically i can heard the motor noise from the opener itself for around 10 seconds then the built in light flashes for.";}}